Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Let me compile the complete implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Comment Replies for PostDetailScreen

### Overview

This plan adds threaded comment replies (single-level nesting) to the PostDetailScreen. It involves changes to two files: the API layer (`socialApi.ts`) and the screen itself (`PostDetailScreen.tsx`). An optional third change adds a `ReplyIcon` to the icon library.

---

### 1. API Changes in `socialApi.ts`

**File:** `C:/Users/johnm/iskrib_mobile_app/apps/mobile/src/lib/api/socialApi.ts`

#### 1a. Modify `addComment` to accept an optional `parentId`

The current `addComment` payload type is:

```typescript
payload: {comments: string; postId: string; receiverId?: string}
```

Change it to:

```typescript
payload: {comments: string; postId: string; receiverId?: string; parentId?: string}
```

The body already uses `JSON.stringify(payload)`, so the `parentId` field will be included automatically when provided. The backend already stores `parent_id` on the `JournalComment` model, so it almost certainly accepts this field in the create payload.

#### 1b. Add a `getReplies` method

Add a new function to fetch replies for a specific parent comment. This follows the same pattern as `getComments` but includes a `parentId` query parameter:

```typescript
async getReplies(
  postId: string,
  parentId: string,
  cursor: string | null = null,
  limit = 20,
): Promise<{comments: JournalComment[]; hasMore?: boolean}> {
  const params = new URLSearchParams();
  params.set('postId', postId);
  params.set('parentId', parentId);
  params.set('limit', String(limit));
  if (cursor) {
    params.set('before', cursor);
  }

  return apiRequest<{comments: JournalComment[]; hasMore?: boolean}>(
    `/getComments?${params.toString()}`,
    {method: 'GET'},
  );
},
```

