### 3. UI Design for PostDetailScreen

**File:** `C:/Users/johnm/iskrib_mobile_app/apps/mobile/src/screens/Home/PostDetailScreen.tsx`

#### 3a. New State Variables

Add these `useState` hooks alongside the existing `commentInput` and other state:

```typescript
// Which comment the user is currently replying to (null = top-level comment)
const [replyingTo, setReplyingTo] = useState<{
  id: string;
  userName: string;
} | null>(null);

// Set of parent comment IDs whose replies are currently expanded
const [expandedReplies, setExpandedReplies] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set());
```

**Why `replyingTo` as an object:** We need both the comment ID (to pass as `parentId`) and the user's name (to show "Replying to @Name" in the input area). Storing both avoids an extra lookup.

**Why a `Set` for `expandedReplies`:** Multiple comments can have their replies expanded simultaneously. A `Set<string>` of parent comment IDs is the most natural and performant structure for toggling.

#### 3b. Reply Data Fetching Strategy

For each expanded parent comment, fetch its replies using a `useQuery` call. Since the number of expanded comment threads is dynamic, the best approach within the existing patterns is to use individual `useQuery` calls inside a child component. The current codebase does NOT use custom hooks with dynamic query lists or `useQueries`, so the cleanest approach is:

**Extract a `CommentThread` component** that renders a single top-level comment and, when expanded, fetches and renders its replies. This component encapsulates its own `useQuery` for replies:

```typescript
function CommentThread({
  comment,
  postId,
  isExpanded,
  isReplyTarget,
  onToggleReplies,
  onReply,
  colors,
}: {
  comment: JournalComment;
  postId: string;
  isExpanded: boolean;
  isReplyTarget: boolean;
  onToggleReplies: (commentId: string) => void;
  onReply: (commentId: string, userName: string) => void;
  colors: Palette;
}) {
  const replyCount = comment.reply_count ?? 0;

  const repliesQuery = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['comment-replies', comment.id],
    queryFn: () => socialApi.getReplies(postId, comment.id, null, 20),
    enabled: isExpanded,   // only fetch when expanded
  });

  const replies = repliesQuery.data?.comments ?? [];

  return (
    <View style={[styles.commentCard, {borderTopColor: colors.borderCard}]}>
      {/* -- Parent comment header + body (same as current) -- */}
      {renderCommentContent(comment, colors)}

      {/* -- Action row: Reply button + Show Replies button -- */}
      <View style={styles.commentActions}>
        <Pressable onPress={() => onReply(comment.id, comment.users?.name || 'User')} hitSlop={8}>
          <Text style={[styles.actionText, {color: colors.textMuted}]}>Reply</Text>
        </Pressable>

        {replyCount > 0 && (
          <Pressable onPress={() => onToggleReplies(comment.id)} hitSlop={8}>
            <Text style={[styles.actionText, {color: colors.accentGold}]}>
              {isExpanded
                ? 'Hide replies'
                : `Show ${replyCount} ${replyCount === 1 ? 'reply' : 'replies'}`}
            </Text>
          </Pressable>
        )}
      </View>

      {/* -- Nested replies (when expanded) -- */}
      {isExpanded && (
        <View style={styles.repliesContainer}>
          {repliesQuery.isLoading ? (
            <ActivityIndicator size="small" color={colors.loaderColor} style={styles.replyLoader} />
          ) : replies.length === 0 ? (
            <Text style={[styles.noRepliesText, {color: colors.textFaint}]}>
              No replies yet.
            </Text>
          ) : (
            replies.map(reply => (
              <View key={reply.id} style={[styles.replyCard, {borderTopColor: colors.borderCard}]}>
                {renderCommentContent(reply, colors)}
              </View>
            ))
          )}
        </View>
      )}
    </View>
  );
}
```

**Key design decisions here:**

- **`enabled: isExpanded`** means React Query only fires the request when the user clicks "Show Replies". The data is then cached automatically (30s stale time per the global config). Collapsing and re-expanding will serve from cache if still fresh.
- **Replies render inline, not in a modal.** This is the standard mobile pattern (Instagram, Twitter/X, Reddit) and works naturally in the existing `ScrollView`.
- **Single level only.** Replies do not show their own "Reply" or "Show Replies" buttons, preventing deep nesting.

#### 3c. Modify the Comment Input to Support Replies

The existing comment input area (lines 327-351) needs minor changes:

1. When `replyingTo` is non-null, show a banner above the `TextInput` indicating "Replying to @Name" with a dismiss (X) button.
2. When submitting, pass `parentId: replyingTo.id` to `addComment` if `replyingTo` is set.
3. On success, clear `replyingTo`, invalidate both the top-level comments query AND the specific reply thread query.

```typescript
const addCommentMutation = useMutation({
  mutationFn: async () => {
    const body = commentInput.trim();
    const receiverId = detailQuery.data?.journal?.user_id ?? detailQuery.data?.journal?.users?.id;
    if (!token) throw new Error('Please log in to comment.');
    if (!body) throw new Error('Comment cannot be empty.');
    if (!receiverId) throw new Error('Missing journal owner.');
    return socialApi.addComment(token, {
      comments: body,
      postId: journalId,
      receiverId,
      parentId: replyingTo?.id,    // <-- NEW: pass parent ID for replies
    });
  },
  onSuccess: () => {
    setCommentInput('');
    const parentId = replyingTo?.id;
    setReplyingTo(null);
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({queryKey: ['journal-comments', journalId]});
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({queryKey: ['journal', journalId]});
    if (parentId) {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({queryKey: ['comment-replies', parentId]});
    }
  },
  onError: e => Alert.alert('Comment failed', e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Error'),
});
```

The reply indicator banner above the text input:

```typescript
{token ? (
  <View style={styles.commentInputRow}>
    {replyingTo && (
      <View style={[styles.replyBanner, {backgroundColor: colors.bgSecondary}]}>
        <Text style={[styles.replyBannerText, {color: colors.textSecondary}]}>
          Replying to {replyingTo.userName}
        </Text>
        <Pressable onPress={() => setReplyingTo(null)} hitSlop={8}>
          <XIcon size={16} color={colors.textMuted} />
        </Pressable>
      </View>
    )}
    <TextInput
      value={commentInput}
      onChangeText={setCommentInput}
      placeholder={replyingTo ? `Reply to ${replyingTo.userName}...` : 'Write a comment...'}
      /* ... rest same as current ... */
    />
    <PrimaryButton
      label={addCommentMutation.isPending ? 'Posting...' : 'Post'}
      onPress={() => addCommentMutation.mutate()}
      disabled={commentInput.trim().length === 0 || addCommentMutation.isPending}
    />
  </View>
) : null}
```

#### 3d. Replace Flat Comment Rendering with CommentThread

Replace the current `comments.map(comment => ...)` block (lines 300-323) with:

```typescript
comments
  .filter(c => !c.parent_id)   // Only render top-level comments
  .map(comment => (
    <CommentThread
      key={comment.id}
      comment={comment}
      postId={journalId}
      isExpanded={expandedReplies.has(comment.id)}
      isReplyTarget={replyingTo?.id === comment.id}
      onToggleReplies={(id) => {
        setExpandedReplies(prev => {
          const next = new Set(prev);
          if (next.has(id)) {
            next.delete(id);
          } else {
            next.add(id);
          }
          return next;
        });
      }}
      onReply={(id, userName) => setReplyingTo({id, userName})}
      colors={colors}
    />
  ))
```

The `.filter(c => !c.parent_id)` is important. If the `getComments` endpoint currently returns both top-level comments AND replies mixed together, this filter ensures we only show top-level ones in the main list. Replies are then fetched separately via `getReplies` when expanded. If the backend already filters by default (only returning `parent_id: null` comments), the filter is a harmless no-op safety measure.

#### 3e. New StyleSheet Entries

Add these styles to the existing `StyleSheet.create` call:

```typescript
